WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:06.959 --> 00:08.917
He does this kind of
amazing thing with his tongue.

00:08.959 --> 00:10.166
( upbeat rock music playing )

00:10.208 --> 00:12.083
I mean, I'm, you know,
a woman in my 40s.

00:12.125 --> 00:14.917
I've had my share of sex.

00:14.959 --> 00:16.959
I've had some...

00:17.000 --> 00:20.041
pretty spectacular...

00:20.083 --> 00:21.583
You know.

00:21.625 --> 00:23.125
I've had sex, okay?

00:23.166 --> 00:26.667
But Sam is this, like...

00:26.709 --> 00:29.834
I don't know. Maybe it's because
I'm in love with him.

00:29.875 --> 00:32.041
No, I don't think it's because
I'm in love with him.

00:32.083 --> 00:33.458
You know,
I was in love with Derek.

00:33.500 --> 00:35.959
I was in love with Mark,

00:36.000 --> 00:39.041
I think,
even for a little while.

00:39.083 --> 00:41.083
No, I think...

00:42.375 --> 00:45.750
it's because
Sam's better than me.

00:45.792 --> 00:48.000
He's a better person.

00:49.583 --> 00:54.208
A genuinely good person.

00:54.250 --> 00:57.000
THERAPIST:
You don't think
you're a good person?

00:59.458 --> 01:02.417
Or maybe it's just that thing
he does with his tongue.

01:07.625 --> 01:09.750
I woke up with a hangover
this morning.

01:12.333 --> 01:14.667
Again.

01:14.709 --> 01:17.041
And I'm just...

01:17.083 --> 01:20.500
I'm over it.

01:20.542 --> 01:23.041
This has to be it.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.875
I don't know why
I was able to put together

01:24.917 --> 01:26.041
almost a decade sober,

01:26.083 --> 01:29.083
and now I can't seem to make it
past about 30 days.

01:30.333 --> 01:31.625
This program gave me a life,

01:31.667 --> 01:35.041
and now I have
a lot to lose, and, uh...

01:35.083 --> 01:37.750
So I'm not drinking today.

01:39.291 --> 01:41.291
Phew.

01:41.333 --> 01:44.208
I can't believe
it is day one again.

01:44.250 --> 01:46.125
( chuckles )

01:47.583 --> 01:49.959
I'm humiliated.

01:54.166 --> 01:58.041
I'm humiliated
that it's day one again.

01:58.083 --> 02:00.000
Um...

02:02.125 --> 02:06.083
But, you know, it's one day
at a time, and, uh...

02:06.125 --> 02:08.959
And I'm not gonna
take a drink today.

02:10.333 --> 02:12.417
Thanks.

02:15.959 --> 02:17.458
ADDISON:
Sorry that I didn't get a chance

02:17.500 --> 02:21.291
to review your case with
Dr. Reilly before the consult.

02:21.333 --> 02:22.750
He has been so amazing.

02:22.792 --> 02:25.917
He's really made me believe
having a child is possible,

02:25.959 --> 02:27.875
despite what
the other doctors said.

02:27.917 --> 02:30.875
Nina's been chasing that miracle
since her mother died last year.

02:30.917 --> 02:34.000
Well,
let's take a look.

02:35.834 --> 02:37.208
Okay.

02:38.750 --> 02:41.417
Oh. It says here you were born
without a uterus?

02:41.458 --> 02:44.333
Yeah. I have Mayer-Rokitansky-
Kuster-Hauser syndrome.

02:44.375 --> 02:46.208
It's a mouthful, right?

02:46.250 --> 02:47.959
Ha, ha. But her ovaries
are functional.

02:48.000 --> 02:50.208
That's the important part.
Right, but you understand--

02:50.250 --> 02:53.041
I mean, Dr. Reilly
explained to you

02:53.083 --> 02:54.709
that you can't
get pregnant?

02:54.750 --> 02:57.083
You have to have a uterus
to carry a child.

02:57.125 --> 03:00.041
I know. That's why Gammy
is giving me hers.

03:00.083 --> 03:01.500
Mm-hm.

03:01.542 --> 03:04.000
( dramatic theme playing )

03:10.083 --> 03:11.625
He's been waking up
a lot at night,

03:11.667 --> 03:13.625
and, uh, he's a little fussier
than usual.

03:13.667 --> 03:16.208
Mm-hm.
Any fever or runny nose?

03:16.250 --> 03:18.667
No.
But he was pulling his ear.

03:18.709 --> 03:20.875
What if he perfed his eardrum?
He could go deaf.

03:20.917 --> 03:23.875
Eardrums are fine,
and he is fine.

03:23.917 --> 03:26.041
And you are...

03:26.083 --> 03:27.250
I-- Ha, ha.

03:27.291 --> 03:31.375
Well, I, um...

03:31.417 --> 03:35.125
I may be going a teensy bit
crazy from all the mommy-ness.

03:35.166 --> 03:37.041
But it's a good crazy.

03:37.083 --> 03:39.041
I have never had
the chance really, you know,

03:39.083 --> 03:44.041
to be at home all the time
alone with my 2-year-old son.

03:44.083 --> 03:46.458
So it's a good crazy.

03:46.500 --> 03:48.208
And, you know,
then there's Pete.

03:48.250 --> 03:49.792
My husband
had a heart attack.

03:49.834 --> 03:51.583
I mean,
listen to that sentence, Coop.

03:51.625 --> 03:53.041
My husband
had a heart attack.

03:53.083 --> 03:57.458
My handsome, studly,
virile husband.

03:58.500 --> 03:59.792
You know
what I think I need?

03:59.834 --> 04:01.875
I think I need
a little perspective.

04:01.917 --> 04:04.667
You know, from people
who are doing what I'm doing.

04:04.709 --> 04:06.041
Mommies.

04:06.083 --> 04:09.041
Do you know any cool mommies
with groups? Mommy groups?

04:09.083 --> 04:11.166
Okay, first of all,
stop saying "mommy."

04:11.208 --> 04:13.583
Second, are you sure
that that's what you want?

04:13.625 --> 04:17.041
Yes, yes. I think it would be
interesting and fun, and--

04:17.083 --> 04:21.709
Come on, Cooper. Tell me
where the cool mommies are.

04:21.750 --> 04:24.041
I haven't been able to sleep
since my heart attack.

04:24.083 --> 04:26.208
I've tried everything:
meditation, self-hypnosis.

04:26.250 --> 04:27.917
You call the therapists
I recommended?

04:27.959 --> 04:30.041
Why would I waste my time
talking to a total stranger?

04:30.083 --> 04:31.709
I know you.
I trust you.

04:31.750 --> 04:33.041
I'm flattered.
You're free.

04:33.083 --> 04:34.125
( both chuckle )

04:34.166 --> 04:35.959
Pete--
Look, do you know

04:36.000 --> 04:38.250
that a third of all
quadruple bypass patients

04:38.291 --> 04:40.458
are dead within ten years?

04:40.500 --> 04:43.333
Well, those kind of numbers
would keep most people awake.

04:43.375 --> 04:45.291
Look, it's normal
to feel scared.

04:45.333 --> 04:46.625
I'm not scared.
I'm pissed.

04:46.667 --> 04:48.041
I did everything right.

04:48.083 --> 04:49.792
I never smoked,
I exercise,

04:49.834 --> 04:52.667
I cut way back on red meat
and dairy, decaf.

04:52.709 --> 04:56.041
And now I eat broccoli.
I hate broccoli.

04:56.083 --> 04:57.291
( chuckles )

04:57.333 --> 04:59.000
How's Violet
handling all this?

04:59.041 --> 05:01.709
Oh, she's terrified.
You can see it in her eyes.

05:01.750 --> 05:03.166
She thinks
I'm gonna drop dead.

05:03.208 --> 05:05.667
Your heart attack
was traumatic for her too.

05:05.709 --> 05:07.333
She'll relax
when she's convinced

05:07.375 --> 05:09.041
that the family's
no longer in crisis.

05:09.083 --> 05:12.542
When will that be?
When you find another therapist.

05:15.125 --> 05:17.750
COOPER:
Hey, can I get some of that?

05:19.375 --> 05:22.166
Really? I've apologized,
like, a thousand times.

05:22.208 --> 05:27.041
I am truly, deeply,
incredibly sorry, Charlotte.

05:27.083 --> 05:29.333
What's going on now?
I--

05:29.375 --> 05:32.041
I did a thing.
A stupid thing.

05:32.083 --> 05:36.500
Yes, a stupid thing that ended
up saving a young girl's life.

05:36.542 --> 05:38.917
And that's the very last time
I'll defend myself,

05:38.959 --> 05:41.333
but come on, Charlotte,
you can't stay mad at me.

05:41.375 --> 05:42.917
You broke into my computer

05:42.959 --> 05:45.291
and stole confidential
information.

05:45.333 --> 05:47.208
Don't bet on it.

05:51.750 --> 05:52.834
Late night?

05:52.875 --> 05:55.333
Chief of staff
and curfew police.

05:55.375 --> 05:58.834
You're a busy woman.
Good morning.

05:58.875 --> 06:00.250
Or not.

06:00.291 --> 06:03.041
Don't mind her. We're all
really happy that you're here.

06:03.083 --> 06:06.000
You promised a patient
a uterine transplant?

06:06.041 --> 06:07.458
What the hell
were you thinking?

06:07.500 --> 06:09.041
Nice welcome wagon
you got there.

06:09.083 --> 06:11.583
It can't be done.
I did work at the Mayo Clinic

06:11.625 --> 06:13.959
on the procedural viability
of uterine organ transplant.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.041
It can be done.
On animals.

06:16.083 --> 06:17.333
It has been done on a human,

06:17.375 --> 06:19.542
just not with
any long-term success.

06:19.583 --> 06:21.166
Somebody has to be the first.
Sam.

06:21.208 --> 06:22.583
JAKE:
Thank you, Sam.

06:22.625 --> 06:24.625
There is always a first.
Nina's a perfect candidate.

06:24.667 --> 06:25.875
She's young, healthy.

06:25.917 --> 06:27.583
She is grieving.
Her mother just died.

06:27.625 --> 06:28.917
She's not thinking clearly.

06:28.959 --> 06:31.709
Look, I'm in no position
to judge her motives.

06:31.750 --> 06:34.667
Where would she get the uterus?
Oh, from her gammy. Yeah.

06:34.709 --> 06:38.041
Her 66-year-old grandmother.
Who's probably not using it.

06:38.083 --> 06:41.041
It puts both women through
an unnecessary, risky surgery.

06:41.083 --> 06:42.375
Even if she survives,
Nina would be

06:42.417 --> 06:44.291
on anti-rejection meds
for months

06:44.333 --> 06:45.917
before you can do
an embryo transfer.

06:45.959 --> 06:48.041
And even then, her body
can reject the uterus,

06:48.083 --> 06:49.709
endangering her
and the fetus.

06:49.750 --> 06:52.917
What about the obvious solution?
You skip the surgery and adopt.

06:52.959 --> 06:55.667
Or you use a surrogate.
JAKE: That's not what she wants.

06:55.709 --> 06:58.458
She wants to give birth
like her mother did her.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.250
It's not my place to judge that.
It's my place

07:00.291 --> 07:02.917
to make it happen if I can,
and I can.

07:02.959 --> 07:06.458
If this works, we can advance
the science of fertility.

07:06.500 --> 07:09.542
The patient's aware of risks,
she has a donor lined up.

07:09.583 --> 07:11.959
I'll take the shot.
I think it's worth a shot.

07:12.000 --> 07:13.750
You wanna stand in her way,

07:13.792 --> 07:15.041
or do you wanna help her
make a baby

07:15.083 --> 07:17.291
and help make history
in the process?

07:20.000 --> 07:22.750
You increased your dosage
without talking to me?

07:22.792 --> 07:25.041
Well, I wasn't
thinking about you

07:25.083 --> 07:27.250
so much as I was
thinking about Eva.

07:27.291 --> 07:29.834
Eva?
She's one of my kindergartners.

07:29.875 --> 07:31.458
She's 5 years old.

07:31.500 --> 07:35.291
Things aren't so great at home
so I spend extra time with her

07:35.333 --> 07:39.709
and I was having
a real impact until...

07:39.750 --> 07:42.542
It's hard to explain Parkinson's
to a 5-year-old.

07:42.583 --> 07:45.458
My hand started tremoring,
and she was fine with that,

07:45.500 --> 07:46.583
but then the--

07:46.625 --> 07:48.041
But then,
the jerking started,

07:48.083 --> 07:50.542
and then, I froze
in front of her.

07:50.583 --> 07:54.041
And that was so scary for her.
It was just awful.

07:54.083 --> 07:56.041
So, yes,
I increased my dosage.

07:56.083 --> 07:58.041
But it seems to really
be working because,

07:58.083 --> 07:59.750
you know,
the symptoms decreased.

07:59.792 --> 08:02.041
Okay, but high doses
of your meds

08:02.083 --> 08:04.083
have been known to cause
pretty serious side effects.

08:04.125 --> 08:06.583
They affect the limbic system,
which is the area of the brain

08:06.625 --> 08:08.750
that deals with
impulse control.

08:08.792 --> 08:12.291
Have you had any impulsive
or compulsive behaviors?

08:12.333 --> 08:16.291
Gambling, risk taking,
anything out of the ordinary?

08:16.333 --> 08:19.041
Um...

08:19.083 --> 08:21.917
My husband is having
a checkup with Sam.

08:21.959 --> 08:24.125
He's probably almost done,
right?

08:25.625 --> 08:28.291
SAM:
Your cortisol levels are way up.
You're stressed.

08:28.333 --> 08:31.709
My 40-year-old wife
has Parkinson's disease.

08:31.750 --> 08:33.917
That's a little stressful.
Yeah, I know.

08:33.959 --> 08:35.959
You're doing a great job
of taking care of her.

08:36.000 --> 08:37.542
Now you gotta take
better care of yourself.

08:37.583 --> 08:38.709
You exercising?

08:38.750 --> 08:40.500
Yeah, I definitely
keep thinking about it.

08:40.542 --> 08:43.125
( both chuckle )

08:43.166 --> 08:44.333
Huh.

08:44.375 --> 08:46.333
( mysterious theme playing )

08:46.375 --> 08:48.542
Sam, what is it?
Uh...

08:48.583 --> 08:51.959
I'm sorry, Will.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.834
I got some bad news.

08:55.083 --> 08:59.166
Laura, symptoms I can help.
But I need to know.

08:59.208 --> 09:01.875
Are you having side effects?
Compulsive behavior?

09:01.917 --> 09:04.542
Sam says I have gonorrhea.

09:04.583 --> 09:06.166
I haven't had sex
with anyone but you.

09:06.208 --> 09:08.166
Can you say the same?

09:08.208 --> 09:13.333
Yes, Dr. Shepherd,
I've been having side effects.

09:13.375 --> 09:16.417
( dramatic theme playing )

09:19.041 --> 09:21.500
It started with a single dad
of one of the kids in my class.

09:21.542 --> 09:25.041
He came in for a parent-teacher
conference and he's--

09:25.083 --> 09:27.166
Um, he's very handsome.

09:27.208 --> 09:30.625
And I noticed he was looking
at my chest while I was talking.

09:30.667 --> 09:32.291
The next thing I know,
my hand is on his pants,

09:32.333 --> 09:34.250
and then in his pants,
and then we're doing it

09:34.291 --> 09:35.834
in the supply closet
in my classroom

09:35.875 --> 09:37.583
on top of the chalk
and the magic markers.

09:37.625 --> 09:39.417
Wow.
Yeah, so--

09:39.458 --> 09:41.709
I mean, it just--
It was that one time,

09:41.750 --> 09:45.458
and I swore
it will never happen again.

09:45.500 --> 09:47.583
Okay. Good.

09:47.625 --> 09:49.166
That's good.
Because we can contact him

09:49.208 --> 09:50.542
and we can have him
treated for--

09:50.583 --> 09:53.250
Then with the janitor
in his supply closet.

09:53.291 --> 09:56.458
And then with the man who came
to fix my dripping faucet.

09:56.500 --> 09:58.041
Your dripping faucet?

09:58.083 --> 10:00.625
The plumber.
Got that.

10:00.667 --> 10:04.625
And I just-- Do you think
that's where the gonorrhea--?

10:04.667 --> 10:05.959
It's hard to say.

10:06.000 --> 10:07.625
This is crazy.
This is not me.

10:07.667 --> 10:11.041
I am married to
a wonderful, wonderful man,

10:11.083 --> 10:13.291
and I can't lose him. God,
I never wanted to hurt him.

10:13.333 --> 10:15.458
I can't live with the tremors,
I can't stop grabbing--

10:15.500 --> 10:18.458
Got it. Got it.

10:18.500 --> 10:22.041
Okay, let's start with
an STD panel and an HIV test,

10:22.083 --> 10:24.959
and then we'll
take it from there.

10:25.000 --> 10:27.083
Okay.

10:28.792 --> 10:30.792
She didn't literally say
"the plumber."

10:30.834 --> 10:33.959
He fixed her leaky faucet.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.792
Think it's funny your patient
destroyed a long-term marriage

10:36.834 --> 10:39.458
with recurrent infidelity?
AMELIA: It's actually sad.

10:39.500 --> 10:41.333
And I'm hoping
her husband understands

10:41.375 --> 10:43.166
that the drugs changed
her brain chemistry,

10:43.208 --> 10:45.291
which changed
her behavior.

10:45.333 --> 10:47.083
I mean, he can't
hold it against her.

10:47.125 --> 10:48.750
( snickers )

10:48.792 --> 10:50.083
"Hold it against her."
( chuckles )

10:50.125 --> 10:52.291
Oh, stop it,
both of you.

10:52.333 --> 10:54.250
So we're saying
infidelity gets excused

10:54.291 --> 10:57.000
when drugs are involved?
In this case, yes.

10:57.041 --> 10:58.500
CHARLOTTE:
Isn't that like saying

10:58.542 --> 11:01.041
you can't blame a drunk driver
after she totals another car?

11:01.083 --> 11:04.083
A drunk driver
chooses to get wasted.

11:04.125 --> 11:05.917
Laura did not choose
Parkinson's.

11:05.959 --> 11:07.917
Will can't blame her
for side effects.

11:07.959 --> 11:11.041
SHELDON:
That doesn't change she was
fooling around with other men.

11:11.083 --> 11:13.834
And you're asking him
to suck it up.

11:13.875 --> 11:15.709
Heh. "Suck it up."

11:15.750 --> 11:17.500
( chuckling )

11:17.542 --> 11:19.041
AMELIA:
Will is devoted to Laura.

11:19.083 --> 11:21.333
And I think
I can save the marriage.

11:21.375 --> 11:23.291
How?
Deep brain stimulation.

11:23.333 --> 11:26.792
Why do you always wanna do DBS?
Because it works.

11:26.834 --> 11:29.333
I stimulate the brain, the
Parkinson's symptoms decrease,

11:29.375 --> 11:31.125
and the pornography
is relegated

11:31.166 --> 11:33.792
to Laura and Will's
television set.

11:33.834 --> 11:36.041
DBS is my magic wand.

11:36.083 --> 11:38.041
( chuckling )

11:38.083 --> 11:40.667
I just kind of
handed you that one.

11:44.709 --> 11:46.667
Hey.
You wanna grab some lunch?

11:46.709 --> 11:48.166
Hmm, I can't.

11:48.208 --> 11:51.625
Then do you want
to mess around?

11:51.667 --> 11:53.166
( chuckles )

11:53.208 --> 11:55.750
Mm. Yes,

11:55.792 --> 11:58.667
but I have an appointment.

11:58.709 --> 12:01.125
That you can't cancel?
That I shouldn't cancel.

12:01.166 --> 12:03.917
I'm-- Mm.

12:03.959 --> 12:07.083
I'm interviewing
a couple of IVF specialists.

12:07.125 --> 12:09.041
Huh.

12:09.083 --> 12:10.583
Cool.
Ha, ha.

12:10.625 --> 12:12.417
Sam, I didn't mean to--
That's fine.

12:12.458 --> 12:13.709
Any other time--

12:13.750 --> 12:15.041
Any other time, I would.
I get it.

12:15.083 --> 12:19.000
I didn't have a condom
on me anyway, so...

12:20.250 --> 12:22.500
Sam, this is weird.
No, it's fine.

12:22.542 --> 12:27.083
You do what you have to do.
And it's-- It's fine. Really.

12:27.125 --> 12:29.000
Yeah?
Mm-hm.

12:29.041 --> 12:31.041
Actually, I'm...

12:31.083 --> 12:32.583
You know,
I'm excited about it.

12:32.625 --> 12:35.041
And I know I don't talk to you
about it much,

12:35.083 --> 12:37.041
but I could if you want.
No, you don't have to.

12:37.083 --> 12:39.083
Are you sure?
Yes, I'm happy for you.

12:39.125 --> 12:41.291
I am happy for you.
But this is your thing.

12:41.333 --> 12:43.125
And I--
Oh, sorry.

12:43.166 --> 12:46.041
Am I, uh, interrupting?
SAM: No.

12:46.083 --> 12:48.667
JAKE:
Well, that's a whole lot
of uterine transplant research

12:48.709 --> 12:50.625
for someone who thinks
it's a crazy procedure.

12:50.667 --> 12:53.250
I am intellectually curious,
but my opinion hasn't changed.

12:53.291 --> 12:54.750
JAKE:
That's a shame
in this case.

12:54.792 --> 12:56.208
The guys on the transplant team,

12:56.250 --> 13:00.750
they're fine for the job,
but I'd prefer you.

13:00.792 --> 13:02.875
Listen, Nina's checking
into the hospital tomorrow.

13:02.917 --> 13:04.083
Go talk to her.

13:04.125 --> 13:06.166
If you're not interested,
I'll leave you alone.

13:06.208 --> 13:08.041
Promise?

13:08.083 --> 13:10.667
You hungry?
Yeah.

13:17.125 --> 13:19.000
Bonjour.

13:19.041 --> 13:21.291
Violet, this is Annette.
She's Daisy's mom.

13:21.333 --> 13:24.041
And this is Lynn.
Little Truman is hers.

13:24.083 --> 13:28.041
And that handsome boy
is my Leo.

13:28.083 --> 13:29.709
What are you drinking,
red or white?

13:29.750 --> 13:31.041
( Violet chuckles )

13:31.083 --> 13:33.166
Don't mind Lynn.
She just stopped breast-feeding,

13:33.208 --> 13:34.959
and so she's making up
for lost time.

13:35.000 --> 13:37.041
Truman turned 3
and lost interest.

