28:34.083 --> 28:36.041
All right, I think
you're being ridiculous.

28:36.083 --> 28:37.375
Oh, wow.
No. I mean,

28:37.417 --> 28:40.041
of course you don't like
any of the mommies

28:40.083 --> 28:41.125
in the mommy group.

28:41.166 --> 28:43.000
You have nothing in common
with these women

28:43.041 --> 28:45.000
other than the fact
that you all have children.

28:45.041 --> 28:47.458
I mean, it would be
like me being friends

28:47.500 --> 28:49.166
with every infertile woman
in town

28:49.208 --> 28:52.250
just because
we can't have kids.

28:52.291 --> 28:54.208
Yes.

28:54.250 --> 28:55.875
Yes, yes.

28:55.917 --> 28:58.667
God. I feel better.
Good.

28:58.709 --> 29:01.333
You know, I mean, here I am,
trying to have a baby,

29:01.375 --> 29:02.875
you know, without Sam.

29:02.917 --> 29:06.041
And that's weird, of course.
We were talking about me still.

29:06.083 --> 29:09.834
We weren't done.
Right. Sorry.

29:09.875 --> 29:11.291
I'm just...

29:13.083 --> 29:15.041
I'm just really lonely.
I am not a mommy-group mommy,

29:15.083 --> 29:16.875
and I'm not allowed to work,

29:16.917 --> 29:19.041
and my husband
had a heart attack.

29:19.083 --> 29:21.583
That's a scary sentence.

29:21.625 --> 29:23.291
Thank you.

29:24.583 --> 29:25.959
Do you wanna be friends?

29:27.083 --> 29:29.041
I mean,
is that what this lunch is?

29:29.083 --> 29:30.333
Do you?

29:32.125 --> 29:34.166
I like your haircut.

29:36.083 --> 29:37.333
I...

29:38.917 --> 29:41.750
I think it's great you wanna
have a kid on your own.

29:41.792 --> 29:44.041
Yeah?
I'm lonely too, you know?

29:44.083 --> 29:46.041
Without Nai,
I'm really lonely.

29:46.083 --> 29:48.875
So we'll be friends.

29:48.917 --> 29:51.291
We'll be friends.

29:57.041 --> 29:58.500
SAM: Hey.
COOPER: Hey, Sam.

29:58.542 --> 30:01.917
How is your relationship going?
Mine is great.

30:01.959 --> 30:04.959
You should really think
about getting married. Mm.

30:06.083 --> 30:08.041
Hey, did you schedule
Laura's surgery yet?

30:08.083 --> 30:09.667
She canceled it.

30:09.709 --> 30:13.041
She is not interested
in changing her behavior.

30:13.083 --> 30:14.250
She wants to sleep around.

30:14.291 --> 30:16.166
She even asked me
to tell her husband

30:16.208 --> 30:18.041
that surgery is not an option.

30:18.083 --> 30:19.125
Well, you can't lie
to the man.

30:19.166 --> 30:21.166
I am well aware of that,
Charlotte,

30:21.208 --> 30:23.041
which is why I'm saying
nothing at all.

30:23.083 --> 30:25.792
So Laura gets a free pass to
cheat on her husband?

30:25.834 --> 30:27.792
How she lives her life,
that's her own business.

30:27.834 --> 30:31.000
She's in a relationship.
No, that's not right.

30:31.041 --> 30:33.041
Once you betray
your partner's trust,

30:33.083 --> 30:35.542
it's hard to get it back.

30:35.583 --> 30:38.709
Wow. You're a bitch
to me and to Cooper.

30:38.750 --> 30:40.125
Who knew you had such range?

30:48.959 --> 30:50.792
JAKE:
Now, that is a beautiful uterus.

30:50.834 --> 30:53.166
Nicely done.
ADDISON: Thank you.

30:53.208 --> 30:55.083
What do you think about
Joanie Matthews?

30:55.125 --> 30:59.041
JAKE:
Uh, she's a bit of
an IVF mad scientist.

30:59.083 --> 31:01.166
Brilliant. Why?

31:01.208 --> 31:03.333
ADDISON:
Just looking around.
Dave Atkins?

31:03.375 --> 31:06.875
Oh, he's real old-school.
Warm, great bedside manner.

31:06.917 --> 31:08.250
I think you should
meet with them both.

31:08.291 --> 31:10.959
Send me a list of who you're
looking at. I'll vet them.

31:11.000 --> 31:13.625
ADDISON: Thank you.
Okay, ladies and gentlemen,

31:13.667 --> 31:16.041
I am going to release
the Kelly.

31:16.083 --> 31:17.667
There we go.

31:17.709 --> 31:19.041
( EKG beeping )

31:19.083 --> 31:21.000
Damn it. Okay. The internal
iliac has retracted.

31:21.041 --> 31:22.250
I need to stop the bleeding.

31:22.291 --> 31:24.750
Gonna have to clamp
the vascular supply proximally.

31:24.792 --> 31:28.000
There's too much blood.
I need you to clear the field.

31:30.083 --> 31:33.458
Damn it. Retracted too far.
I need to embolize the vessel.

31:33.500 --> 31:36.500
Cross her for six units
and hang the FFP.

31:36.542 --> 31:39.375
If you embolize, it's gonna cut
supply to the transplant.

31:39.417 --> 31:40.875
JAKE:
If I don't, I'll lose Nina.

31:40.917 --> 31:42.458
Come on, Nina.
Hang in there.

31:44.083 --> 31:45.000
Hang in there now.

31:49.083 --> 31:52.041
( soft dramatic theme playing )

31:52.083 --> 31:54.041
You fought one hell
of a fight in there, cowboy.

31:54.083 --> 31:55.291
( chuckles )

31:55.333 --> 31:56.500
Lost, though.

31:56.542 --> 31:57.917
Look, you tried,

31:57.959 --> 31:59.709
which is more than
most doctors would've done.

31:59.750 --> 32:02.041
It's more than
I would've done.

32:02.083 --> 32:04.041
You saved her life.
That's a win.

32:04.083 --> 32:06.291
Not for me, it isn't.

32:12.458 --> 32:14.875
There.
VIOLET: Yeah, silly Pooh.

32:16.250 --> 32:19.458
Hey. Um, hey, before you go,
I was thinking

32:19.500 --> 32:22.208
I wanna give the nanny
a few more hours.

32:22.250 --> 32:25.041
I wanna start another book.
I think it'd be good for me.

32:25.083 --> 32:26.291
Lucas is gonna need therapy

32:26.333 --> 32:28.458
when he's old enough
to read the first one.

32:28.500 --> 32:30.458
Come on, Pete.
You're in the office every day.

32:30.500 --> 32:33.667
You get to use your training,
your intellect.

32:33.709 --> 32:35.250
Every part of you
is engaged.

32:35.291 --> 32:37.041
And, uh, I want that too.
I need it.

32:37.083 --> 32:39.041
I can't believe it.
Already bored with motherhood.

32:39.083 --> 32:41.709
You don't think that raising
our child is important work.

32:41.750 --> 32:44.542
Of course it is. But I don't
see why I have to do it

32:44.583 --> 32:46.041
to the exclusion
of everything else.

32:46.083 --> 32:49.667
It's important Lucas sees
a woman who's well-rounded--

32:49.709 --> 32:51.583
A 2-year-old
doesn't want well-rounded.

32:51.625 --> 32:54.291
A 2-year-old
wants his mother.

32:54.333 --> 32:57.500
So long, pal. Bye.

32:57.542 --> 33:00.041
It's not like I've been
at home for the past two years.

33:00.083 --> 33:04.041
Why is it such a shock I would
wanna work and raise my child?

33:04.083 --> 33:06.000
What the hell
is going on with you?

33:07.083 --> 33:08.500
I'm late for work.

33:11.959 --> 33:15.709
I'm sorry, Nina.
I'm so sorry.

33:15.750 --> 33:17.834
But we knew
this was a long shot, right?

33:17.875 --> 33:19.083
We knew that,
but we tried anyway,

33:19.125 --> 33:21.417
because that was
important to you.

33:23.083 --> 33:25.917
You're young, you have
the support of your family,

33:25.959 --> 33:27.500
and you will be a mother.

33:27.542 --> 33:31.083
We can explore surrogacy now
or you can adopt.

33:31.125 --> 33:33.041
But I wanted to be
like my mom.

33:33.083 --> 33:36.041
I know. And if your mom
were here right now,

33:36.083 --> 33:38.041
she would tell you that
it wasn't giving birth to you

33:38.083 --> 33:39.917
that defined her.

33:39.959 --> 33:42.583
It was the first time you
looked in her eyes and smiled.

33:42.625 --> 33:46.792
It was the first time
you fell asleep on her shoulder

33:46.834 --> 33:49.792
and she'd barely
let herself breathe

33:49.834 --> 33:52.000
because she never wanted
that moment to end.

33:54.083 --> 33:57.625
You will have your baby,

33:57.667 --> 33:59.041
however she comes
into the world,

33:59.083 --> 34:02.041
and you will love her
incredibly well,

34:02.083 --> 34:04.083
because your mom
taught you how.

34:05.667 --> 34:07.458
And that's all that matters.

34:07.500 --> 34:11.000
Okay?
That's all that matters.

34:13.291 --> 34:15.208
Hi.
Hey.

34:15.250 --> 34:18.000
Thanks for, uh--
Thanks for meeting me here.

34:18.041 --> 34:20.250
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, is there a reason

34:20.291 --> 34:22.125
we couldn't meet
at the office?

34:22.166 --> 34:26.792
Well, I was just hoping to,
uh, speak to you as a friend

34:26.834 --> 34:28.625
rather than a doctor.

34:28.667 --> 34:30.083
Um...
Okay.

34:30.125 --> 34:34.208
I don't understand why or how
you could do this to Will.

34:35.750 --> 34:39.792
Well, that's because
you and I aren't friends.

34:39.834 --> 34:42.041
Fair enough. Uh...

34:42.083 --> 34:43.667
Well, what about
20 years of marriage?

34:43.709 --> 34:45.375
That's gotta mean something.

34:45.417 --> 34:47.291
With these meds,
I don't have a really great

34:47.333 --> 34:49.000
editing mechanism anymore.
Okay.

34:49.041 --> 34:52.166
So I'm just gonna say
some things. Uh...

34:52.208 --> 34:54.250
My husband won't have sex

34:54.291 --> 34:56.709
outside of
the missionary position.

34:56.750 --> 34:58.083
And if he finishes
before I do,

34:58.125 --> 35:00.375
he rolls over
and he goes to sleep.

35:00.417 --> 35:02.291
Early on in our marriage,

35:02.333 --> 35:04.625
when he caught me
trying to finish

35:04.667 --> 35:09.041
after he was done,
he called me disgusting.

35:09.083 --> 35:11.917
Disgusting.
So he has some issues.

35:11.959 --> 35:15.041
In this particular area,
he has issues.

35:15.083 --> 35:18.125
And his issues
have become my issues.

35:18.166 --> 35:19.709
Mm-hm.
That's what happens

35:19.750 --> 35:21.041
in a marriage.
That's right.

35:21.083 --> 35:23.875
And he has no interest
in dealing with those issues.

35:23.917 --> 35:27.709
And for the first time,
I understand that,

35:27.750 --> 35:33.583
because I have no interest in
dealing with mine.

35:33.625 --> 35:36.542
I mean,
we make a great team.

35:36.583 --> 35:40.500
On so many levels, we're--
We're a great team.

35:40.542 --> 35:44.500
So don't judge me.
Please.

35:44.542 --> 35:46.667
You're not
inside my marriage.

35:46.709 --> 35:50.166
And you can't be inside
anybody else's marriage, either.

35:50.208 --> 35:52.000
You have to know that.

35:52.041 --> 35:55.041
Appearances,
they mean nothing.

35:55.083 --> 35:56.959
Clearly.

35:57.000 --> 35:58.500
Look at me.

36:01.417 --> 36:03.583
PETE:
She leaves us
every chance she gets

36:03.625 --> 36:05.041
for these rooms
full of strangers,

36:05.083 --> 36:07.917
who are desperate to tell her
what a difference she made.

36:07.959 --> 36:10.041
Violet decided to go
on the book tour.

36:10.083 --> 36:11.709
She wants to write.
Not the same thing.

36:11.750 --> 36:14.041
Well, it feels the same.
Don't be such a baby.

36:14.083 --> 36:15.709
Excuse me?

36:15.750 --> 36:17.041
You want the benefit
of my expertise,

36:17.083 --> 36:18.125
as a friend, without paying?

36:18.166 --> 36:20.333
Well, with that
comes the truth.

36:20.375 --> 36:22.041
What are you afraid of, Pete?

36:22.083 --> 36:24.500
Sheldon, I worked
in Bosnia in a war zone.

36:24.542 --> 36:26.500
I'm in the chaos of the ER
every day.

36:26.542 --> 36:28.917
I'm not a guy that gets scared.
I told you. I'm angry.

36:28.959 --> 36:31.166
I know what you told me,
but a 14-year-old boy

36:31.208 --> 36:33.959
who's dumped with foster
families isn't just angry.

36:34.000 --> 36:36.250
And the disconnect you feel,
that's not about anger.

36:38.208 --> 36:40.041
So, what are you afraid of?

36:40.083 --> 36:43.083
( dramatic theme playing )

36:44.792 --> 36:46.750
( soft theme playing )

36:46.792 --> 36:50.041
Hey. Uh, I think
you were right.

36:50.083 --> 36:53.375
One of my favorite sentences
in the world.

36:53.417 --> 36:54.959
Right about what?
About Laura.

36:55.000 --> 36:58.625
I talked to her, and, uh,
I guess it is her business.

36:58.667 --> 37:01.333
You know, what she's doing
and what she tells Will.

37:01.375 --> 37:03.959
It's not easy, but sometimes
the truth is worse.

37:04.000 --> 37:05.750
Yeah.

37:05.792 --> 37:09.375
So I guess she'll have her high,
he won't know,

37:09.417 --> 37:11.834
and hopefully...

37:11.875 --> 37:13.458
It'll be better that way.

37:19.709 --> 37:21.500
( playing ascending scales )

37:31.750 --> 37:34.041
I'm drowning here, Charlotte.

37:34.083 --> 37:36.166
And I obviously don't know
what to do to save myself,

37:36.208 --> 37:37.709
and every time
I try to say anything,

37:37.750 --> 37:39.875
it's like tying another
cinder block to my ankle.

37:39.917 --> 37:45.041
So if you just tell me
what to do, I will do it,

37:45.083 --> 37:47.500
whatever it is, happily.

37:47.542 --> 37:49.917
Seriously, come on.
Tell-- Tell me.

37:49.959 --> 37:52.750
Come on. Tell me.

37:52.792 --> 37:53.917
Tell me.
Stop it.

37:53.959 --> 37:57.500
You made me
be the sheriff with you.

37:57.542 --> 38:00.041
It sucks being the sheriff.
I'm good at it.

38:00.083 --> 38:02.375
Everybody already thinks I'm
the Wicked Witch of St. Ambrose.

38:02.417 --> 38:03.875
Everyone who?
Everyone-- Amelia?

38:03.917 --> 38:06.667
Look, I don't care.
It's fine. It's my job.

38:06.709 --> 38:08.041
The job isn't
about making friends.

38:08.083 --> 38:10.041
But you're my husband.

38:10.083 --> 38:13.000
Don't make me be the sheriff
with you too.

38:15.083 --> 38:16.458
Look...

38:18.083 --> 38:22.041
I don't regret saving Kerri.

38:22.083 --> 38:23.083
I don't.

38:23.125 --> 38:26.333
But I do regret
not having your back.

38:26.375 --> 38:30.709
I will never put you
in that position again,

38:30.750 --> 38:33.291
and I will not make you
be the sheriff.

38:33.333 --> 38:35.333
( tender theme playing )

38:48.000 --> 38:51.041
We should be able to tell
each other anything, right?

38:51.083 --> 38:53.333
That sounds like the prelude
to something bad.

38:53.375 --> 38:55.333
No, no.
No, it's not bad.

38:55.375 --> 38:57.041
Sam.
I--

38:57.083 --> 38:58.917
If you have something
to tell me...

38:58.959 --> 39:02.041
No, no, no. It's not me.
It's you. It's yesterday.

39:02.083 --> 39:04.583
You wanted to talk to me
about the IVF stuff,

39:04.625 --> 39:08.083
and I, uh, I cut you off.

39:08.125 --> 39:09.375
And I'm sorry.

39:09.417 --> 39:11.709
It's okay.
No, it's not okay.

39:11.750 --> 39:15.375
We're together and, you know,
we shouldn't have secrets

39:15.417 --> 39:17.166
or, you know,
things that we're thinking about

39:17.208 --> 39:19.333
that we can't say.

39:19.375 --> 39:21.750
Agreed.

39:21.792 --> 39:25.000
Okay, good. So tell me--

39:25.041 --> 39:26.959
Tell me about the IVF,
the doctors.

39:27.000 --> 39:29.417
Is there anybody
that you like? Um...

39:29.458 --> 39:31.166
Sam.

39:31.208 --> 39:32.917
Mm.

39:34.041 --> 39:35.750
Thank you.

39:35.792 --> 39:40.041
But really, I'm fine.

39:40.083 --> 39:42.041
Okay.

39:42.083 --> 39:43.875
( slow pop music playing )

40:07.083 --> 40:08.291
I'm afraid you think
I'm a bad mother

40:08.333 --> 40:10.000
and that you don't
love me enough.

40:13.083 --> 40:16.041
I'm afraid I'll die before
I'm done raising Lucas.

40:21.500 --> 40:24.417
I renamed the practice.
Did I tell you?

40:24.458 --> 40:28.583
Seaside Health and Wellness.

40:28.625 --> 40:30.458
I thought about calling it
Montgomery Wellness.

40:30.500 --> 40:32.417
Bizzy would've told me
to do that.

40:32.458 --> 40:35.291
It is all of my money
funding the place now.

40:35.333 --> 40:38.917
But I didn't do it.

40:38.959 --> 40:43.625
It is a cooperative practice,
and the name reflects that.

40:43.667 --> 40:45.041
A few years ago, I...

40:45.083 --> 40:47.625
THERAPIST:
You would've gone with
"Montgomery."

40:47.667 --> 40:51.417
Yeah. I would have.

40:51.458 --> 40:53.041
So...

40:53.083 --> 40:55.458
You know, no matter what,
whatever happens,

40:55.500 --> 40:58.041
Sam has rubbed off on me.

40:58.083 --> 41:01.375
His goodness, his kindness,

41:01.417 --> 41:03.917
his honesty,

41:03.959 --> 41:08.500
his generosity of spirit...

41:08.542 --> 41:10.375
has rubbed off.

41:11.792 --> 41:13.834
( both chuckling )

41:15.083 --> 41:17.166
Hello.

41:18.333 --> 41:20.125
See you at lunch.

41:23.125 --> 41:26.041
Cooper?
Yes.

41:26.083 --> 41:28.375
You don't remember me,
do you?

41:28.417 --> 41:32.041
No. I'm sorry,
have we met?

41:32.083 --> 41:34.792
Nine years ago. I was
tending bar at the Key Club.

41:34.834 --> 41:37.291
You came in,
stayed till last call.

41:37.333 --> 41:40.041
We had sex in my SUV
in the parking lot.

41:40.083 --> 41:42.041
( chuckles )

41:42.083 --> 41:45.083
Erica.
Hi, Erica.

41:45.125 --> 41:47.417
Yeah, hi. Awkward.

41:47.458 --> 41:51.041
Yeah.
Uh, I'm married now.

41:51.083 --> 41:52.458
I have a son.

41:55.083 --> 41:57.291
He's 8.

41:57.333 --> 41:59.250
COOPER:
Mm-hm.

42:00.417 --> 42:02.709
His name is Mason.

42:02.750 --> 42:04.625
And he's...

42:04.667 --> 42:07.041
And this is...

42:07.083 --> 42:09.375
This is really not what I...

42:09.417 --> 42:11.041
Anyway, ahem...

42:11.083 --> 42:13.000
He's-- Well...

42:15.083 --> 42:16.625
He's yours.

42:29.291 --> 42:31.917
( mellow theme playing )
